# My Life - a Guide for Kids With Diabetes
#### Helping a child with diabetes to understand their condition can be tough
sometimes. But you’re not alone. My Life is a free guide to type 1 diabetes
The My Life crew, Ella, Jack, Nadeem and Liz, will take your child through
everything they need to know, from understanding their type 1 diagnosis, to
diet, to going back to school and everything in between. Plus there's stories
from other kids with diabetes, puzzles and fun facts.
Order your free copy of the My Life Guide
> "I enjoyed reading other children’s stories when I read My Life in hospital
> because it helped me understand what it was going to be like living with
> diabetes myself.” Leah, aged 10, was diagnosed with type 1 diabetes a year
Already got your copy of My Life? Have a go at the puzzles and let us know how
You might be feeling overwhelmed or worried about the future if your child has
been recently diagnosed. We want you to know that we're here for you every
We've got a free, termly My Life magazine coming out that you will be able to
And you'll be able to sign up for our parents' newsletter, with advice, news
and stories from other families living with type 1 diabetes to help you feel
We'll update this page with more information on how to sign up soon, so keep
We've got loads of information for parents on our children and diabetes pages.
You can read about everything from coping with a type 1 diagnosis as a family,
to using insulin pens and pumps and managing your child's diabetes at school.
You can also contact a local support group or join our online forum to chat to
And our helpline is always available if you've got any questions or worries or
just want to talk to someone who 'gets' it.
